<br>
Regrowth for heals, nurture for buffing your group, and nature is for pets, DoTs and DS.<br>
<br>
Also, later on as you approach your teens you'll realize that your weapons will become less and less important to you, especially in a group.  For example, in your teens, even high teens, you'll only be able to hit in the low teens, while other classes of the same lvl hits in the 30s as do mobs.  You'll never out last a mob hitting you that hard when you're hitting for 10-15.  Not to mention that you'll be spending so much time healing that you won't have a chance to melee anyways, so don't worry too much about investing in nice weapons.  Instead, invest in nice armor, and perhaps a nice shield.<br>
<br>
When you get to 10th lvl and can wear reinforced armor, try to buy them from other players or make them yourself instead of buying them from merchants.  Although buying merchants is a LOT more affordable in DAoC than in EQ, you'll still get a bit of a break (sometimes not by much though) from buying from other players. <p><CENTER>
